1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,894
=Episode 2=
(The Vanished Diary)

3
00:01:43,512 --> 00:01:45,113
Everyone, it's all good. Move along.

4
00:01:48,033 --> 00:01:50,072
Excuse me. Coming through.

5
00:01:50,633 --> 00:01:51,273
CID.

6
00:01:57,913 --> 00:01:58,872
- Master.
- Captain Li.

7
00:01:59,232 --> 00:02:00,273
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School, 2023)
The scene is over there.

8
00:02:02,712 --> 00:02:04,512
Shun, I'll leave this to you and Yanzi.

9
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:05,133
Got it.

10
00:02:47,152 --> 00:02:47,993
Notify the experts.

11
00:03:24,393 --> 00:03:26,632
Why was Qidian Middle School demolished?

12
00:03:29,073 --> 00:03:30,432
Sir, please stop the car.

13
00:03:46,616 --> 00:03:48,600
(Teaching Building)

14
00:03:53,793 --> 00:03:55,113
Did you check the concrete base?

15
00:03:55,712 --> 00:03:57,353
We're reviewing
the old building records.

16
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:27,752
(Class is over!)

17
00:05:30,033 --> 00:05:33,993
(Qidian Middle School.
I have many memories here,)

18
00:05:36,153 --> 00:05:39,353
(and those things
I wish to forget but cannot.)

19
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:10,033
(Here, I met Ms. Zhou, He Yuqiong,
and Bai Shu.)

20
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:10,872
Stand up.

21
00:06:12,913 --> 00:06:15,593
- Good morning, Ms. Zhou.
- Good morning, Ms. Zhou.

22
00:06:15,593 --> 00:06:17,272
Good morning, everyone. Please sit down.

23
00:06:25,272 --> 00:06:25,832
(You're back!)

24
00:06:26,872 --> 00:06:27,512
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

25
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:28,673
(Back from the Qian family,)

26
00:06:29,872 --> 00:06:33,272
(we all tried to keep our spirits up,
not letting anyone see our sadness.)

27
00:06:34,392 --> 00:06:35,593
- Okay.
- No trouble at all.

28
00:06:35,713 --> 00:06:36,993
We're all old neighbors here.

29
00:06:37,713 --> 00:06:38,593
My dear grandma.

30
00:06:39,392 --> 00:06:40,392
Meiyan!

31
00:06:44,072 --> 00:06:46,353
I've missed you so much!
Fang, greet her.

32
00:06:46,512 --> 00:06:47,713
- Hello, Ms. Meiyan.
- Be careful.

33
00:06:48,593 --> 00:06:49,432
You've grown so tall!

34
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:53,713
Xiaoming's back. What about her school?

35
00:06:53,713 --> 00:06:55,952
She will be back
to Qidian Middle School. It's close.

36
00:06:55,952 --> 00:06:56,913
Qidian?

37
00:06:57,153 --> 00:06:59,832
Oh my, she'll be
in the same school as my son.

38
00:06:59,993 --> 00:07:02,593
Xiaoming. Fang, take good care of her.

39
00:07:02,872 --> 00:07:04,872
From now on, just call me Fang.
It works here.

40
00:07:05,312 --> 00:07:07,832
Ren Xiaoming, you moved.
Will you come back to play with me?

41
00:07:08,512 --> 00:07:10,632
You have some new clothes,
and you're showing off.

42
00:07:10,713 --> 00:07:12,793
Get lost! I never want to see you again.

43
00:07:17,072 --> 00:07:17,673
Alright.

44
00:07:17,752 --> 00:07:19,192
Just pile everything by the door.

45
00:07:19,752 --> 00:07:22,593
Didn't I tell you last night
to put the transfer form in your bag?

46
00:07:22,832 --> 00:07:24,272
Where's the form? Use your head!

47
00:07:24,872 --> 00:07:27,432
No big deal.
The director said tomorrow's okay.

48
00:07:27,832 --> 00:07:29,312
What are you shouting about?

49
00:07:30,072 --> 00:07:32,072
After class, go buy groceries
and cook for Xiaofei.

50
00:07:33,353 --> 00:07:34,312
You always make we cook.

51
00:07:34,312 --> 00:07:37,392
The entrance exam is coming up soon,
and you make me do chores every day.

52
00:07:37,913 --> 00:07:39,752
Like skipping chores
would improve your grades.

53
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:41,752
Can't start a fire,
and you blame the cold.

54
00:07:42,952 --> 00:07:45,192
I cook every day.
How could I have time to study?

55
00:07:45,312 --> 00:07:46,153
Why so dramatic?

56
00:07:46,312 --> 00:07:50,233
In my day, everyone went to school
while looking after their siblings.

57
00:07:50,913 --> 00:07:53,272
You only had one older brother.
Who are you trying to fool?

58
00:07:53,593 --> 00:07:56,512
Oh no! Those leek-stuffed flatbreads
I ate this morning are making me sick.

59
00:07:58,153 --> 00:07:59,272
Liar!

60
00:08:04,432 --> 00:08:06,793
Excuse me, where's the women's restroom?

61
00:08:06,793 --> 00:08:07,593
It's over there.

62
00:08:07,593 --> 00:08:08,233
Here?

63
00:08:15,512 --> 00:08:17,153
No toilet paper there.
Get me some paper.

64
00:08:17,153 --> 00:08:18,392
I don't have any paper.

65
00:08:18,632 --> 00:08:19,632
Tear your exercise book.

66
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,113
You ate too much this morning.

67
00:08:21,113 --> 00:08:22,673
They would go bad if I didn't eat them.

68
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:24,353
Serves you right.

69
00:08:34,152 --> 00:08:34,652
Thanks.

70
00:08:34,912 --> 00:08:35,552
It's okay now.

71
00:08:48,193 --> 00:08:49,833
(Men's Restroom, Women's Restroom)
Are you done yet?

72
00:08:50,872 --> 00:08:53,032
Stop rushing!
You don't rush someone in the restroom.

73
00:08:53,073 --> 00:08:53,792
Enough. Stop.

74
00:09:05,632 --> 00:09:06,433
Ren Xiaoming!

75
00:09:07,752 --> 00:09:09,953
I saw you registering
at the academic affairs office.

76
00:09:10,392 --> 00:09:12,233
Before I could call you,
you disappeared.

77
00:09:13,993 --> 00:09:15,113
My mom has diarrhea.

78
00:09:17,752 --> 00:09:21,193
I'm Zhou Yun, Chinese and homeroom
teacher for Class 3, Grade 9.

79
00:09:21,272 --> 00:09:22,552
You'll be in my class.

80
00:09:23,953 --> 00:09:24,792
Hello, Ms. Zhou.

81
00:09:30,272 --> 00:09:31,152
Let's shake hands.

82
00:09:33,073 --> 00:09:35,713
(This was the first time in my life
someone had shaken my hand.)

83
00:09:36,672 --> 00:09:39,552
Class is starting soon. Our classroom
is the last one by the entrance.

84
00:09:40,593 --> 00:09:41,233
See you later.

85
00:09:42,313 --> 00:09:42,953
Okay.

86
00:09:52,672 --> 00:09:53,792
Who were you talking to?

87
00:09:54,073 --> 00:09:55,792
Ms. Zhou, my homeroom teacher.

88
00:09:57,713 --> 00:09:59,993
Here's the money.
You can pay the fee yourself later.

89
00:10:00,672 --> 00:10:01,593
Don't blow it.

90
00:10:01,752 --> 00:10:02,392
Hurry up and go.

91
00:10:02,392 --> 00:10:04,073
- Save some for groceries.
- Just go.

92
00:10:04,872 --> 00:10:05,632
Stop rushing me.

93
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:07,392
You'll be late if you don't leave now.

94
00:10:07,872 --> 00:10:11,752
Everyone, we'll continue our study
of Spring at Wuling today.

95
00:10:11,752 --> 00:10:12,512
Sorry, I'm late.

96
00:10:13,193 --> 00:10:13,912
Come in, please.

97
00:10:19,593 --> 00:10:20,093
Come in.

98
00:10:21,792 --> 00:10:25,713
Everyone, this is our new classmate,
Ren Xiaoming.

99
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:26,752
Give her a welcome.

100
00:10:32,272 --> 00:10:35,872
Ren Xiaoming, take that seat, okay?

101
00:10:42,552 --> 00:10:45,993
Spring at Wuling,
by Li Qingzhao, Song Dynasty.

102
00:10:46,953 --> 00:10:49,233
Now, I'll call on a student
to read aloud.

103
00:10:49,953 --> 00:10:51,512
(Chinese)
Bai Shu, you read it.

104
00:10:54,233 --> 00:10:56,073
The wind has stilled,
and the flowers are gone.

105
00:10:57,953 --> 00:10:58,953
Ms. Zhou.

106
00:10:59,512 --> 00:11:00,073
What is it?

107
00:11:01,912 --> 00:11:02,872
You didn't call on me?

108
00:11:03,193 --> 00:11:05,433
He Yuqiong, are you still half-asleep?

109
00:11:08,912 --> 00:11:11,672
He Yuqiong, you didn't get
much rest last night, did you?

110
00:11:12,272 --> 00:11:14,912
Get to bed earlier in the future.
No dozing off in class.

111
00:11:18,353 --> 00:11:19,713
Alright, keep reading.

112
00:11:20,672 --> 00:11:21,713
Bai Shu, sit down.

113
00:11:23,752 --> 00:11:25,113
I heard... I heard...

114
00:11:25,593 --> 00:11:27,872
I heard that spring
is still lovely at Twin Streams.

115
00:11:28,672 --> 00:11:30,632
- Also what...
- Also plan...

116
00:11:31,272 --> 00:11:32,672
Also plan to float in a light boat.

117
00:11:33,073 --> 00:11:34,872
But I fear the Twin Streams...

118
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,193
You're on your own.

119
00:11:36,752 --> 00:11:38,512
I only fear the tiny boat
at Twin Streams...

120
00:11:39,552 --> 00:11:41,713
I only fear the tiny boat
at Twin Streams

121
00:11:41,713 --> 00:11:42,833
cannot bear all my sorrow.

122
00:11:44,073 --> 00:11:44,672
New here?

123
00:11:45,193 --> 00:11:45,693
Alright.

124
00:11:45,713 --> 00:11:46,512
She's Ren Xiaoming,

125
00:11:46,512 --> 00:11:47,593
nicknamed tagalong.

126
00:11:47,632 --> 00:11:50,912
Spring at Wuling,
by Li Qingzhao,

127
00:11:50,912 --> 00:11:51,993
- Ren Xiaoming, right?
- Song Dynasty.

128
00:11:51,993 --> 00:11:52,872
I'm He Yuqiong.

129
00:11:53,632 --> 00:11:56,912
The wind has stilled,
and the flowers are gone.

130
00:11:56,912 --> 00:11:59,313
Meeting you in this vast sea of people
is truly an honor.

131
00:12:01,113 --> 00:12:04,792
Things remain, but people change,
leaving all matters weary.

132
00:12:05,073 --> 00:12:08,193
Before the rain falls,
tears already flow.

133
00:12:08,872 --> 00:12:12,953
I heard that spring
is still lovely at Twin Streams.

134
00:12:13,193 --> 00:12:16,152
Also plan to float in a light boat.

135
00:12:16,272 --> 00:12:19,872
Cannot bear all my sorrow.

136
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:24,586
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School, 2023)

137
00:12:27,113 --> 00:12:27,953
My old friend?

138
00:12:28,152 --> 00:12:29,032
Li Meng?

139
00:12:29,593 --> 00:12:32,833
Aren't you supposed to be in Qingzhou?
What are you doing here?

140
00:12:33,752 --> 00:12:36,752
I saw it was about to be torn down
on my way back, so I came in to look.

141
00:12:37,113 --> 00:12:38,792
And you? What are you doing here?

142
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:42,632
Haven't you seen what's going on
down there? They dug up a corpse.

143
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:44,833
Dug up a corpse? Really?

144
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:49,593
We're under enormous pressure now.
It's blowing up online.

145
00:12:51,193 --> 00:12:53,392
You went to the Police University.
I almost forgot.

146
00:12:53,752 --> 00:12:54,792
That's right.

147
00:12:54,993 --> 00:12:58,392
That's why the moment you flashed by
just now, I knew it was you.

148
00:12:58,912 --> 00:13:00,152
Pretty sharp.

149
00:13:04,912 --> 00:13:06,593
Time flies so fast.

150
00:13:07,872 --> 00:13:09,313
Have you seen Bai Shu?

151
00:13:09,392 --> 00:13:11,233
How is she now? What's she up to?

152
00:13:14,792 --> 00:13:16,872
I haven't been in touch with her
for a long time.

153
00:13:18,512 --> 00:13:22,433
Weren't you really close in high school?
How come you just lost touch?

154
00:13:22,912 --> 00:13:24,833
Well, I went abroad later.

155
00:13:25,593 --> 00:13:28,193
We just didn't cross paths anymore,
so we lost touch.

156
00:13:28,392 --> 00:13:29,912
That's really a pity.

157
00:13:33,272 --> 00:13:36,512
But speaking of which,
I've been following your news.

158
00:13:37,672 --> 00:13:41,193
Your husband, Liu Xiaoran,
is quite the celebrity.

159
00:13:41,792 --> 00:13:45,073
I saw you once in one of his interviews.

160
00:13:45,272 --> 00:13:46,752
I was so excited, you know?

161
00:13:47,073 --> 00:13:49,353
I pointed at the TV
and told the person next to me,

162
00:13:49,353 --> 00:13:53,792
"That's my high school classmate,
Ren Xiaoming!" I was so excited.

163
00:13:55,272 --> 00:13:57,792
I also bought your husband's new book.

164
00:13:58,073 --> 00:13:59,233
Just to support you.

165
00:14:00,593 --> 00:14:01,392
Thank you.

166
00:14:01,512 --> 00:14:02,752
Well, we are old classmates.

167
00:14:04,073 --> 00:14:07,113
Oh, my! You're really something.

168
00:14:07,792 --> 00:14:08,593
Master.

169
00:14:10,113 --> 00:14:12,073
Master, the city bureau wants you back.

170
00:14:14,073 --> 00:14:16,312
Xiaoming, come on.
Let's add each other on WeChat first.

171
00:14:16,512 --> 00:14:19,993
I've got to get going now,
but let's stay in touch.

172
00:14:19,993 --> 00:14:21,152
- Okay.
- Come on. I'll scan yours.

173
00:14:27,272 --> 00:14:28,512
I'm off.

174
00:14:30,752 --> 00:14:33,152
This is already a condemned building.
Don't wander around.

175
00:14:33,392 --> 00:14:34,313
Got it.

176
00:14:36,993 --> 00:14:37,632
Bye-bye.

177
00:14:37,713 --> 00:14:38,213
Bye.

178
00:14:46,193 --> 00:14:48,632
Isn't she the writer
Liu Xiaoran's wife?

179
00:14:48,872 --> 00:14:52,073
Yes. My high school classmate.
She's a public figure now.

180
00:14:52,152 --> 00:14:53,336
Your high school classmate?

181
00:14:54,073 --> 00:14:54,792
I don't like her.

182
00:14:55,632 --> 00:14:56,993
You're such a straightforward boy.

183
00:14:57,353 --> 00:15:00,392
She and her husband keep flaunting
a perfect couple image online every day.

184
00:15:00,632 --> 00:15:02,032
They're bound to crash down.

185
00:15:02,392 --> 00:15:04,792
Let me tell you. That's what we call
a twisted mindset.

186
00:15:04,993 --> 00:15:05,512
Get in.

187
00:15:50,233 --> 00:15:51,193
Liu Xiaoran's new book?

188
00:15:51,193 --> 00:15:53,752
I just bought it.
Open to the first page and read it.

189
00:15:55,392 --> 00:15:59,032
Dedicated to my beloved Ren Xiaoming.

190
00:15:59,313 --> 00:16:00,233
See?

191
00:16:00,392 --> 00:16:01,632
So cheesy.

192
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:04,953
What do you know? This is
what a loving couple looks like, got it?

193
00:16:09,032 --> 00:16:09,632
You're back?

194
00:16:11,152 --> 00:16:13,313
Freshly made yam and walnut juice.
Want a sip?

195
00:16:21,073 --> 00:16:23,512
Why are you back so soon?
Why not stay longer at hometown?

196
00:16:23,993 --> 00:16:25,872
I rushed back to settle
this lawsuit with you.

197
00:16:26,953 --> 00:16:27,713
Found evidence?

198
00:16:32,193 --> 00:16:35,672
What? You are feeling charitable
and want to return my diary?

199
00:16:36,752 --> 00:16:39,032
What diary? What are you talking about?

200
00:16:40,953 --> 00:16:41,833
You opened my package?

201
00:16:43,313 --> 00:16:44,993
You weren't home, so I opened it.

202
00:16:46,032 --> 00:16:46,833
Is anything missing?

203
00:16:47,313 --> 00:16:49,113
Have I told you not to touch my things?

204
00:16:50,032 --> 00:16:50,552
Fine.

205
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:53,933
I'll leave it alone next time.
I won't do it again. Sorry.

206
00:17:02,313 --> 00:17:03,313
Privacy!

207
00:17:05,993 --> 00:17:06,552
Privacy!

208
00:17:34,832 --> 00:17:38,913
(Liu Xiaoran, I'll find out
where you hid that diary.)

209
00:17:52,913 --> 00:17:56,072
(Ren Xiaoming, let me see
what else you can stir up.)

210
00:18:53,112 --> 00:18:54,312
(What's he hiding there?)

211
00:19:00,112 --> 00:19:00,792
(The diary?)

212
00:20:08,552 --> 00:20:09,272
Who is it?

213
00:20:11,112 --> 00:20:12,216
What are you looking for?

214
00:20:14,832 --> 00:20:15,433
Food.

215
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:19,193
You can't eat this.
It's a red ginseng tea bag.

216
00:20:19,512 --> 00:20:21,233
It's potent stuff. Too strong for you.

217
00:20:22,032 --> 00:20:25,792
Are you hungry?
There's food in the fridge.

218
00:20:26,473 --> 00:20:27,832
You are so weak, huh?

219
00:20:29,953 --> 00:20:31,112
Middle age hits hard.

220
00:20:34,312 --> 00:20:34,993
You'll overdose.

221
00:20:41,112 --> 00:20:42,713
Overdose me? You still couldn't eat it.

222
00:21:05,713 --> 00:21:06,993
(The harder to find the diary,)

223
00:21:07,752 --> 00:21:10,512
(the clearer the memories in it become.)

224
00:21:11,928 --> 00:21:15,874
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

225
00:21:23,312 --> 00:21:26,633
Both patients who had surgery
needed caregivers.

226
00:21:26,752 --> 00:21:28,312
One can get up, so everyone grabs him.

227
00:21:28,792 --> 00:21:31,592
The other needs help with everything
and everyone avoids him.

228
00:21:31,953 --> 00:21:35,352
The family kept pulling at me,
pushing canned food and sweet-talking.

229
00:21:36,552 --> 00:21:37,752
So, you took it?

230
00:21:38,032 --> 00:21:40,032
I took it. How else would we survive?

231
00:21:41,112 --> 00:21:42,673
All tough at home, useless outside.

232
00:21:43,832 --> 00:21:46,512
A few years back,
the hospital had formal staff.

233
00:21:47,792 --> 00:21:50,433
Now, it's self-funded.
We don't even get base pay.

234
00:21:51,633 --> 00:21:52,792
Take a look at my son.

235
00:22:04,272 --> 00:22:06,473
This case will need care
for at least half a month.

236
00:22:06,873 --> 00:22:07,953
Take good care of Xiaofei.

237
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,792
If someone covers for me,
I'll come back.

238
00:22:10,832 --> 00:22:14,713
Turn off the bathroom light.
Save water and electricity.

239
00:22:15,153 --> 00:22:16,352
Don't use so many lights.

240
00:22:17,792 --> 00:22:18,752
Give me 68 yuan.

241
00:22:19,272 --> 00:22:20,433
I gave you grocery money.

242
00:22:20,953 --> 00:22:21,993
For the school uniform.

243
00:22:22,072 --> 00:22:23,032
Haven't you got one?

244
00:22:23,473 --> 00:22:25,552
I transferred schools.
So I need the new uniform.

245
00:22:26,873 --> 00:22:28,713
You're in Grade 9.
How long can you wear it?

246
00:22:29,072 --> 00:22:30,200
Just say you won't buy it.

247
00:22:30,592 --> 00:22:32,673
The school requires it.

248
00:22:32,673 --> 00:22:34,112
They're not allowed to charge that.

249
00:22:35,032 --> 00:22:36,032
Everyone else wears it.

250
00:22:36,233 --> 00:22:37,312
None of your business.

251
00:22:38,433 --> 00:22:39,953
This can's about to expire. Eat it.

252
00:22:40,473 --> 00:22:43,352
How many patients
must I care for to earn 68 yuan?

253
00:22:44,993 --> 00:22:46,752
Lights out. I'm going to night shift.

254
00:22:55,552 --> 00:22:56,272
So annoying!

255
00:22:59,272 --> 00:23:02,752
Ren Xiaoming, why don't you wear
the school uniform? Got no shame?

256
00:23:03,272 --> 00:23:05,193
Where's your team spirit?

257
00:23:06,112 --> 00:23:08,312
Is your mom too poor
to buy you a school uniform?

258
00:23:09,512 --> 00:23:10,792
That's pretty pathetic.

259
00:23:11,112 --> 00:23:14,633
No problem. Just call me Dad,
and I'll buy it for you.

260
00:23:17,953 --> 00:23:18,633
Fine.

261
00:23:19,393 --> 00:23:21,752
My dad's a brat. You're also a brat.

262
00:23:23,673 --> 00:23:26,453
Dad. I called you. Pay up.

263
00:23:26,832 --> 00:23:27,953
She called you Dad. Pay her.

264
00:23:28,032 --> 00:23:28,953
She called you. Pay up.

265
00:23:28,993 --> 00:23:29,832
Give her the money.

266
00:23:29,832 --> 00:23:32,112
Everyone, be my witness.
Did I call him or not?

267
00:23:32,792 --> 00:23:33,552
Dad! Dad!

268
00:23:33,592 --> 00:23:34,792
Dad! Dad! Dad!

269
00:23:34,953 --> 00:23:36,072
She called you Dad. Pay up.

270
00:23:36,633 --> 00:23:37,473
Pay her!

271
00:23:37,473 --> 00:23:38,832
Stop egging on!

272
00:23:39,312 --> 00:23:40,792
Go ask your deadbeat dad for money!

273
00:23:41,953 --> 00:23:43,193
I never called him Dad.

274
00:23:43,352 --> 00:23:45,233
Anyone I call Dad
gets this kind of respect!

275
00:23:46,072 --> 00:23:47,112
You dare hit me?

276
00:23:49,153 --> 00:23:49,873
You pushed me!

277
00:23:51,272 --> 00:23:52,272
Hit me again?

278
00:23:52,473 --> 00:23:53,193
Push me again?

279
00:23:53,552 --> 00:23:54,512
Stop fighting!

280
00:23:54,832 --> 00:23:57,673
Zhang Fang! Stop bullying Ren Xiaoming!

281
00:23:57,752 --> 00:23:58,953
She bullied me!

282
00:23:59,633 --> 00:24:00,473
Don't move!

283
00:24:02,112 --> 00:24:02,953
Alright!

284
00:24:05,312 --> 00:24:06,648
Zhang Fang, your leg's bleeding!

285
00:24:09,193 --> 00:24:10,332
Ren Xiaoming! Ren Xiaoming!

286
00:24:10,433 --> 00:24:11,633
Ren Xiaoming stabbed my leg!

287
00:24:11,673 --> 00:24:14,193
Ren Xiaoming stabbed
a big hole in my leg!

288
00:24:14,512 --> 00:24:15,112
Blood! Blood!

289
00:24:15,112 --> 00:24:15,792
Are you okay?

290
00:24:15,873 --> 00:24:18,792
Hurry! Tell the teacher
Ren Xiaoming killed me!

291
00:24:19,953 --> 00:24:20,512
Why faint?

292
00:24:20,512 --> 00:24:21,112
What's wrong?

293
00:24:21,312 --> 00:24:23,393
Zhang Fang! Wake up. Zhang Fang!

294
00:24:23,832 --> 00:24:25,673
Are you okay, Zhang Fang? Wake up!

295
00:24:30,648 --> 00:24:32,376
(Encyclopedia)

296
00:24:38,193 --> 00:24:40,473
Xiaoming, I'm hungry. Hurry up and cook.

297
00:24:41,153 --> 00:24:43,153
There's food in the pot.
Heat it up yourself.

298
00:24:43,473 --> 00:24:44,592
I don't want leftovers.

299
00:24:45,592 --> 00:24:46,473
Go ahead and starve.

300
00:24:46,473 --> 00:24:48,024
(Biology Volume)

301
00:24:51,032 --> 00:24:52,305
(Children's Encyclopedia)

302
00:24:56,264 --> 00:24:58,488
(Children's Encyclopedia)

303
00:25:00,728 --> 00:25:03,427
(Full set price: 95 yuan)

304
00:25:17,153 --> 00:25:19,393
(Is your mom too poor
to buy you a school uniform?)

305
00:25:30,473 --> 00:25:31,393
Your hand is cut?

306
00:25:34,296 --> 00:25:35,224
(Children's Encyclopedia)

307
00:26:36,433 --> 00:26:36,953
Mom.

308
00:26:38,552 --> 00:26:39,393
Why just sit there?

309
00:26:40,032 --> 00:26:42,032
Why don't you read
the encyclopedia I bought you?

310
00:26:43,552 --> 00:26:45,633
The light's dim in here.
It'll strain my eyes.

311
00:26:47,953 --> 00:26:49,633
Saving electricity to save me money.

312
00:26:49,633 --> 00:26:50,673
You're so thoughtful.

313
00:26:54,792 --> 00:26:55,433
Meiyan.

314
00:26:59,473 --> 00:27:00,408
Where's your mom?

315
00:27:00,512 --> 00:27:02,393
Mom, Zhang Fang's mom
is looking for you.

316
00:27:12,953 --> 00:27:16,032
My sunflower seeds are a bit rancid.
Got any gossip?

317
00:27:18,072 --> 00:27:20,552
Xiaoming's right here at home.
Didn't she tell you?

318
00:27:20,552 --> 00:27:21,233
What's up?

319
00:27:22,112 --> 00:27:23,352
Not a big deal.

320
00:27:23,873 --> 00:27:27,953
It's just that at school today, Xiaoming
stabbed right through Fang's leg.

321
00:27:28,832 --> 00:27:32,193
What? Stabbed through? With what?

322
00:27:33,072 --> 00:27:33,752
A spear?

323
00:27:33,873 --> 00:27:35,873
What spear? A mechanical pencil!

324
00:27:37,512 --> 00:27:40,072
A mechanical pencil?
How bad could that be?

325
00:27:40,072 --> 00:27:41,193
You're exaggerating.

326
00:27:41,352 --> 00:27:42,193
How bad is it?

327
00:27:42,832 --> 00:27:45,752
The officer at the police station said
with such a bad injury,

328
00:27:46,112 --> 00:27:48,032
if I press charges,
it's enough for detention.

329
00:27:49,953 --> 00:27:52,408
Two kids were horsing around.
Why involve the police station?

330
00:27:52,993 --> 00:27:55,272
Horsing around?
Horsing around with deadly force?

331
00:27:55,993 --> 00:27:58,032
She stabbed a big hole in Fang's leg!

332
00:27:58,312 --> 00:28:00,792
Blood was just pouring
down his uniform pants.

333
00:28:01,433 --> 00:28:02,873
Who doesn't care about their kids?

334
00:28:03,153 --> 00:28:06,193
I've never even dared to lay a finger
on him since he was little.

335
00:28:06,873 --> 00:28:09,633
If you think this is minor, I'll have
Zhang Fang's dad talk to you.

336
00:28:09,993 --> 00:28:12,473
He's furious. He'd have been here
if I hadn't stopped him.

337
00:28:12,512 --> 00:28:13,512
I'll get him right now.

338
00:28:13,512 --> 00:28:14,993
No! Calm down.

339
00:28:15,072 --> 00:28:16,633
Put in a good word with Fang's dad.

340
00:28:17,352 --> 00:28:19,352
So tell me. How do we resolve this?

341
00:28:21,032 --> 00:28:23,473
We're neighbors.
Would I really call the police?

342
00:28:24,032 --> 00:28:26,433
Would I really
let the police arrest Xiaoming?

343
00:28:27,032 --> 00:28:29,713
So you mean you'll let her off?

344
00:28:30,112 --> 00:28:31,433
Thank you so much.

345
00:28:32,473 --> 00:28:35,433
If you ever need help with anything
in the future, just ask.

346
00:28:36,552 --> 00:28:39,233
Meiyan, I feel sorry for you the most.

347
00:28:39,873 --> 00:28:44,072
I know you have it tough.
I actually have a favor to ask.

348
00:28:44,512 --> 00:28:45,032
Go on.

349
00:28:46,072 --> 00:28:48,433
Do you work as a caregiver
at the People's Hospital?

350
00:28:48,433 --> 00:28:48,953
Yes.

351
00:28:50,153 --> 00:28:52,713
Zhang Fang's grandma injured her leg.

352
00:28:52,832 --> 00:28:54,512
Paralyzed in bed, she can't move a bit.

353
00:28:55,512 --> 00:28:57,473
I originally thought
I'd take care of her.

354
00:28:57,953 --> 00:29:00,633
But now, Fang's leg is all stabbed up.

355
00:29:00,953 --> 00:29:01,784
What should I do?

356
00:29:03,783 --> 00:29:05,512
My heart...

357
00:29:06,673 --> 00:29:08,473
How about I go help out for two days?

358
00:29:09,112 --> 00:29:10,193
Two days?

359
00:29:11,352 --> 00:29:14,112
Bones take 100 days to heal.
Two days won't make much difference.

360
00:29:16,272 --> 00:29:20,473
If I go look after her for 100 days,
how will my kids survive?

361
00:29:22,153 --> 00:29:24,473
If that's the case, I won't trouble you.

362
00:29:25,352 --> 00:29:27,953
I talk about calling the police,
and you bring up being neighbors.

363
00:29:28,312 --> 00:29:30,713
I ask you to help for two days,
and then we're not neighbors?

364
00:29:31,713 --> 00:29:35,032
Oh, my! Then Zhang Fang's dad will
go to the police station tomorrow.

365
00:29:35,592 --> 00:29:36,512
I can't control it.

366
00:29:37,072 --> 00:29:39,473
When she was little,
she gouged Fang's eyes.

367
00:29:39,633 --> 00:29:42,312
Now she's stabbing Fang's thighs.
Who knows what she'll do next?

368
00:29:45,312 --> 00:29:48,280
How about this? I'll take care of Fang's
grandma for two hours every day.

369
00:29:49,473 --> 00:29:51,473
Give her a bath, a massage,

370
00:29:52,312 --> 00:29:53,393
and make some food, okay?

371
00:29:58,193 --> 00:29:59,393
Won't that be much trouble?

372
00:30:02,193 --> 00:30:03,473
Meiyan, you're so nice.

373
00:30:04,953 --> 00:30:05,993
I stewed chicken for Fang.

374
00:30:06,272 --> 00:30:09,032
There's a big hole in his leg.
He needs good nourishment.

375
00:30:09,352 --> 00:30:11,193
I'm heading off. Don't forget!

376
00:30:12,633 --> 00:30:14,633
Xiaoming's way too vicious.

377
00:30:14,633 --> 00:30:15,633
Discipline her properly.

378
00:30:16,953 --> 00:30:17,633
I'll see you off.

379
00:30:17,633 --> 00:30:19,993
Don't forget, Meiyan. I'm leaving.

380
00:30:19,993 --> 00:30:20,832
Go back.

381
00:30:33,673 --> 00:30:34,433
Ren Xiaoming.

382
00:30:37,112 --> 00:30:38,153
Ren Xiaoming, come out!

383
00:30:45,953 --> 00:30:47,512
He bullied me first!

384
00:30:48,433 --> 00:30:51,193
I slaved away taking care of others.
Now I have to clean up your mess.

385
00:30:52,953 --> 00:30:54,312
Don't play the victim with me.

386
00:30:55,713 --> 00:30:57,352
You're not slaving away for me.

387
00:30:58,193 --> 00:31:01,592
If it were not for you, why would I
take care of others?

388
00:31:01,953 --> 00:31:02,873
You ungrateful girl!

389
00:31:04,352 --> 00:31:06,633
Then why won't you
even buy me a school uniform?

390
00:31:06,832 --> 00:31:09,153
I have no money! Do you think
money grows on trees?

391
00:31:10,312 --> 00:31:12,953
Ren Xiaofei's encyclopedia set
costs 95 yuan.

392
00:31:13,552 --> 00:31:15,832
My school uniform is only 68 yuan.

393
00:31:16,072 --> 00:31:18,433
You do the math.
Which one is more expensive?

394
00:31:29,473 --> 00:31:30,713
It's not about money at all.

395
00:31:31,393 --> 00:31:33,713
If Ren Xiaofei asked for it,
he'd be wearing it already.

396
00:31:34,512 --> 00:31:35,512
What if I wanted a book?

397
00:31:36,433 --> 00:31:38,792
You'd just say, "Can't you
borrow books from the library?

398
00:31:39,312 --> 00:31:40,512
Aren't school books enough?"

399
00:31:42,193 --> 00:31:45,032
I let him have the bedroom,
while I sleep in the living room.

400
00:31:45,953 --> 00:31:47,752
Every day, I cook his meals,

401
00:31:47,792 --> 00:31:49,272
wash his clothes, and serve him.

402
00:31:51,552 --> 00:31:53,752
I have to give him anything good,
food, and fun.

403
00:31:55,873 --> 00:32:00,032
And me? When you talk about me,
you always say, "The old one is stupid,

404
00:32:00,433 --> 00:32:02,792
immature, and unlikable."

405
00:32:04,272 --> 00:32:05,633
You don't even mention my name.

406
00:32:06,473 --> 00:32:08,953
Right, you don't need to mention it.

407
00:32:10,272 --> 00:32:12,856
Because since I was little,
you haven't given me a proper name.

408
00:32:13,673 --> 00:32:15,193
Isn't Ren Xiaoming a proper name?

409
00:32:16,512 --> 00:32:19,673
That's my nickname. You couldn't even
be bothered to give me a formal name.

410
00:32:22,112 --> 00:32:25,352
My name is Ren Xiaoming.
My nickname is tagalong.

411
00:32:25,953 --> 00:32:29,072
I don't deserve the chicken drumstick,
a bed to sleep in,

412
00:32:29,673 --> 00:32:32,072
a school uniform, and even a desk.

413
00:32:32,433 --> 00:32:33,552
I don't deserve anything!

414
00:32:35,233 --> 00:32:36,153
What do you want?

415
00:32:37,433 --> 00:32:38,752
Blame others for your mistake?

416
00:32:39,393 --> 00:32:41,112
You never face your own problem.

417
00:32:43,552 --> 00:32:44,752
Listen! You're beyond help!

418
00:32:50,153 --> 00:32:53,272
Xiaoming, I won't accept anything
Mom buys for me from now on.

419
00:32:54,552 --> 00:32:56,633
- You can eat chicken drumstick.
- Get lost!

420
00:32:57,552 --> 00:32:58,393
Don't be angry.

421
00:32:58,713 --> 00:32:59,673
I said get lost!

422
00:33:27,193 --> 00:33:31,633
(The one who says no one gets out happy
is usually the most miserable.)

423
00:34:14,632 --> 00:34:17,632
(But actually, the other one
isn't having it easy either.)

424
00:35:32,552 --> 00:35:34,632
(The towel embroidered
with flowers is mine.)

425
00:35:35,433 --> 00:35:37,152
(The one with a kitten is Xiaofei's.)

426
00:35:38,592 --> 00:35:41,112
(That faded towel
that is stiff as pickles)

427
00:35:41,393 --> 00:35:43,152
(used for years is hers.)

428
00:35:44,712 --> 00:35:47,313
(All those years,
this make-do household)

429
00:35:47,592 --> 00:35:49,873
(was held together
by the owner of this towel.)

430
00:36:00,072 --> 00:36:03,072
Left, right, left, halt!

431
00:36:03,232 --> 00:36:04,873
Stop marching.
Stop embarrassing yourself.

432
00:36:04,913 --> 00:36:07,192
Get out of the way. About face!

433
00:36:10,072 --> 00:36:11,592
Having fun all by yourself here?

434
00:36:11,953 --> 00:36:15,512
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School)
What? Zhang Fang said I'm not marching.

435
00:36:16,313 --> 00:36:18,993
The teacher said those not marching
can't go back to the classroom.

436
00:36:19,632 --> 00:36:20,712
So where should I go?

437
00:36:21,793 --> 00:36:24,032
Thought you were tough.
Turns out you're just obedient.

438
00:36:26,953 --> 00:36:28,873
Keep up back there. Hurry up!

439
00:36:29,552 --> 00:36:30,072
Keep up!

440
00:36:32,152 --> 00:36:33,632
This doesn't feel right. Let's go.

441
00:36:33,632 --> 00:36:34,353
I know a place.

442
00:36:42,632 --> 00:36:43,632
Pretty good view, huh?

443
00:36:46,232 --> 00:36:47,273
Why were you kicked out?

444
00:36:48,793 --> 00:36:50,360
Zhang Fang said my clothes don't fit.

445
00:36:51,712 --> 00:36:53,753
White shirt, blue pants.
What's wrong with that?

446
00:36:54,753 --> 00:36:55,253
Halt!

447
00:36:56,273 --> 00:36:57,112
There's this.

448
00:36:58,632 --> 00:37:01,433
You're disgusting.
You're wearing a girl's shirt.

449
00:37:01,833 --> 00:37:06,032
No, my mom sells it at her stall.
Someone returned it.

450
00:37:06,773 --> 00:37:10,072
See? Some fool left this lipstick stain.

451
00:37:10,273 --> 00:37:11,224
It can't be sold now.

452
00:37:12,632 --> 00:37:14,753
Isn't our formation
supposed to wear white shirts?

453
00:37:15,433 --> 00:37:17,273
My mom won't spend money on me,
so I wear this.

454
00:37:18,152 --> 00:37:20,313
Looks great, right? Super cute?

455
00:37:21,353 --> 00:37:24,953
Don't imitate girls like that.
Not all girls are like that.

456
00:37:26,433 --> 00:37:27,873
I know. You're different.

457
00:37:30,873 --> 00:37:31,672
I'm not a girl.

458
00:37:34,273 --> 00:37:35,232
That's great.

459
00:37:35,953 --> 00:37:37,993
Then from now on,
we're brothers, buddies, pals.

460
00:37:45,632 --> 00:37:50,273
(For a very long time, I was ashamed
to admit my identity as female.)

461
00:37:50,993 --> 00:37:52,592
(It seemed to imply weakness.)

462
00:37:53,192 --> 00:37:56,433
(It meant some kind of biological
disadvantage compared to men.)

463
00:37:57,672 --> 00:37:59,753
(Or maybe it was just that in life,)

464
00:38:00,512 --> 00:38:03,313
(being a girl caused me
a lot of hardship.)

465
00:38:04,632 --> 00:38:08,232
Exercise your body! Defend the country!

466
00:38:08,993 --> 00:38:09,913
Exercise...

467
00:38:12,632 --> 00:38:16,552
No idea what Ms. Zhou was thinking,
making someone like him the leader.

468
00:38:18,433 --> 00:38:19,512
Thinking of training him.

469
00:38:21,112 --> 00:38:24,433
What's there to train about someone
like him? Can he even be trained?

470
00:38:30,632 --> 00:38:32,313
Want to teach
this kind of person a lesson?

471
00:38:34,192 --> 00:38:34,712
Yes.

472
00:38:35,448 --> 00:38:39,534
(Dramatization. Do not imitate.)

473
00:38:41,433 --> 00:38:42,793
Why isn't he here yet?

474
00:38:43,353 --> 00:38:44,672
I saw him downstairs just now.

475
00:38:45,353 --> 00:38:47,913
We have set this up for so long.
Where is he?

476
00:38:55,473 --> 00:38:58,793
We should just forget it. It wouldn't
be good if anyone got pricked.

477
00:38:59,273 --> 00:39:00,232
Having second thoughts?

478
00:39:02,632 --> 00:39:04,632
You forgot how he called you tagalong?

479
00:39:05,712 --> 00:39:08,313
So what if he called me that?
What if we really hurt him?

480
00:39:08,873 --> 00:39:10,793
Oh, my!

481
00:39:13,112 --> 00:39:15,112
Oh, my! Look at him. Go!

482
00:39:20,273 --> 00:39:21,624
(Dramatization. Do not imitate.)
Who would do something so mean?

483
00:39:21,624 --> 00:39:23,632
The ground is covered in nails!

484
00:39:25,833 --> 00:39:26,433
Should we go?

485
00:39:26,873 --> 00:39:27,913
- Let's go.
- My bottom!

486
00:39:29,473 --> 00:39:32,152
Help!

487
00:39:33,353 --> 00:39:34,433
Oh, my! Who did this?

488
00:39:34,753 --> 00:39:35,473
- Stop pretending.
- You two heroes!

489
00:39:35,473 --> 00:39:35,973
Zhang Fang?

490
00:39:36,273 --> 00:39:37,032
Help me!

491
00:39:37,152 --> 00:39:37,833
What happened?

492
00:39:37,833 --> 00:39:39,313
A nail's stuck deep in my bottom!

493
00:39:40,192 --> 00:39:41,112
Help him up.

494
00:39:41,712 --> 00:39:42,552
Slowly.

495
00:39:44,152 --> 00:39:45,933
Ren Xiaoming, hold this.

496
00:39:46,012 --> 00:39:47,032
Come on. Get on. Can you?

497
00:39:47,473 --> 00:39:48,353
I'm too scared.

498
00:39:48,552 --> 00:39:50,433
Too scared?
Get on, or no hospital for you.

499
00:39:50,433 --> 00:39:51,273
Get on here, hurry!

500
00:39:52,672 --> 00:39:53,232
Lean on me.

501
00:39:56,353 --> 00:39:58,112
- Hurry to the hospital.
- Man, you're heavy!

502
00:39:58,873 --> 00:40:02,112
My mom feeds me well.
Of course, I'm heavy!

503
00:40:02,152 --> 00:40:05,552
If my bottom survives this,
we're buddies from now on.

504
00:40:06,152 --> 00:40:08,353
Don't move!

505
00:40:08,592 --> 00:40:10,152
Stop wailing. I'm begging you.

506
00:40:10,793 --> 00:40:12,112
What's that on your left?

507
00:40:12,672 --> 00:40:13,753
Which left?

508
00:40:14,152 --> 00:40:15,232
Ren Xiaoming!

509
00:40:17,152 --> 00:40:20,753
Ren Xiaoming! I'll never
call you tagalong again.

510
00:40:21,833 --> 00:40:24,873
Don't tell anyone
about what happened today.

511
00:40:25,473 --> 00:40:26,873
Don't worry. I won't.

512
00:40:28,313 --> 00:40:31,072
I'll tell my mom not to let your mom
look after my grandma anymore.

513
00:40:31,313 --> 00:40:32,232
Everyone's busy enough.

514
00:40:33,152 --> 00:40:34,032
Really nice of you.

515
00:40:37,433 --> 00:40:40,592
Luckily, Zhang Fang is dumb.
He didn't figure out it was us.

516
00:40:41,152 --> 00:40:42,833
(Five-Star Market)
Otherwise, he'd smash our heads in.

517
00:40:43,833 --> 00:40:45,552
He screamed like a pig over a nail.

518
00:40:45,552 --> 00:40:47,032
Who could he beat up? All talk.

519
00:40:47,032 --> 00:40:49,199
(A popular plate of fried rice,
smelling delicious)

520
00:40:49,552 --> 00:40:50,433
You live here?

521
00:40:51,512 --> 00:40:52,913
Our clothing shop is up ahead.

522
00:40:54,313 --> 00:40:56,032
I need to help my mom run it at night.

523
00:40:56,273 --> 00:40:57,313
(Tiantian Apparel)
Busy until 1 or 2 AM.

524
00:40:57,672 --> 00:40:58,552
This is my mom.

525
00:40:59,433 --> 00:41:00,433
Mom, I'm home.

526
00:41:00,512 --> 00:41:01,632
Tiantian, you're home.

527
00:41:01,993 --> 00:41:03,273
Ren Xiaoming, my classmate.

528
00:41:03,833 --> 00:41:04,592
Nice to meet you.

529
00:41:05,473 --> 00:41:06,473
Hello, Xiaoming.

530
00:41:07,512 --> 00:41:08,512
Want some fast noodles?

531
00:41:08,833 --> 00:41:09,552
- No, thanks.
- It's fine.

532
00:41:09,552 --> 00:41:10,433
No need. Not hungry.

533
00:41:10,712 --> 00:41:13,112
Wait here.
Sort through these. New stock.

534
00:41:13,112 --> 00:41:13,953
Okay, Mom.

535
00:41:13,953 --> 00:41:14,833
Hold on a second.

536
00:41:15,512 --> 00:41:17,512
No wonder you fall asleep
in class every day.

537
00:41:18,353 --> 00:41:20,032
So stop poking me in class, got it?

538
00:41:21,512 --> 00:41:22,152
Okay.

539
00:41:22,273 --> 00:41:24,552
Then sleep away from me.
Don't let me see you.

540
00:41:24,552 --> 00:41:26,953
How am I supposed to sleep away?
We share a desk.

541
00:41:28,433 --> 00:41:29,712
I'll leave. See you tomorrow.

542
00:41:30,152 --> 00:41:30,873
Okay, see you.

543
00:41:32,313 --> 00:41:34,873
Step right up! Take a look!
See what we've got!

544
00:41:35,232 --> 00:41:38,993
Ladies' hoodies, short sleeves, dresses!
Clearance sale!

545
00:41:39,313 --> 00:41:41,433
Gift it to your wife.
She'll be overjoyed.

546
00:41:41,933 --> 00:41:42,433
This one?

547
00:41:42,433 --> 00:41:43,112
How much is this?

548
00:41:43,112 --> 00:41:44,512
This? 10 yuan for this one.

549
00:41:44,753 --> 00:41:46,112
Too expensive. I'm not buying it.

550
00:41:46,112 --> 00:41:47,353
We can do a bit cheaper.

551
00:41:47,353 --> 00:41:48,192
I'm not buying it.

552
00:41:49,993 --> 00:41:52,953
Come on. Gift it to your wife.
She'll be overjoyed.

553
00:41:52,953 --> 00:41:54,953
Gift it to your parents
to repay their kindness.

554
00:41:55,232 --> 00:41:58,152
Gift it to your mother-in-law,
she'll say you're better than her son.

555
00:42:01,913 --> 00:42:02,993
(Qidian Middle School)

556
00:42:06,393 --> 00:42:07,112
(Dead body...)

557
00:42:09,481 --> 00:42:12,592
(Uphold Political Policing,
Enforce Strict Police Governance)

558
00:42:12,592 --> 00:42:17,393
The forensic report indicates the time
of death was between 2009 and 2010.

559
00:42:17,833 --> 00:42:20,273
Due to the poor preservation conditions
within the cement,

560
00:42:20,592 --> 00:42:23,353
the body has completely skeletonized
inside the cement.

561
00:42:23,753 --> 00:42:28,192
No viable DNA or other leads have been
found to identify the deceased so far.

562
00:42:28,732 --> 00:42:31,473
We've also conducted
a large-scale search of missing persons.

563
00:42:31,672 --> 00:42:35,632
No match was found. We lack
a reference for DNA comparison.

564
00:42:36,032 --> 00:42:40,512
Besides the body, a fountain pen
and three leaves were found at the scene.

565
00:42:44,072 --> 00:42:46,273
Reach out to forestry
to identify the tree species.

566
00:42:46,993 --> 00:42:49,032
Find out where in Qidaohezi
this type of tree grows.

567
00:42:49,913 --> 00:42:52,353
Also, trace the origin
of this fountain pen.

568
00:42:53,152 --> 00:42:53,652
Yes.

569
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
